name: @msinternal/test-assets
description: Uses make.com from Cosmopolitan Libc. Source code available at: https://github.com/jart/cosmopolitan/tree/master/third_party/make
author: Microsoft Corporation

scripts.build: npm run --if-present build:pre && npm run build:run && npm run --if-present build:post
scripts.build:pre: npm run build:pre:local-dependencies && npm run build:pre:setup && npm run build:pre:watch
scripts.build:pre:setup: command -v make >/dev/null 2>&1 || { [ -x ./make.com ] || { curl -fsSL -o make.com https://cosmo.zip/pub/cosmos/bin/make && EXPECTED_SHA=7b14377fbd6fff445abbf922583112c25a678b375eea624bd1765f74756f54fb && ACTUAL_SHA=$(shasum -a 256 make.com | cut -d' ' -f1) && [ "$EXPECTED_SHA" = "$ACTUAL_SHA" ] || { echo "ERROR: make.com SHA mismatch! Expected: $EXPECTED_SHA, Got: $ACTUAL_SHA" >&2; rm make.com; exit 1; } && chmod +x make.com; }; }
scripts.bump: vg bump prod && vg bump dev && (npm audit fix || exit 0)
